  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How much would it roughly cost to start a new car company?",
  "response": "Starting a new car company is a massive endeavor and involves substantial financial investment. The costs can vary widely based on several factors such as the scale of the operation, the type of vehicles being produced, geographical location, existing infrastructure, and more. Here are some key areas where costs are involved:\n\n1. **Research and Development (R&D):**\n   Developing a new car, especially if it's innovative or electric, requires significant investment in R&D. This includes designing, prototyping, and testing. Costs here can range from tens of millions to hundreds of millions of dollars.\n\n2. **Manufacturing Facilities:**\n   Setting up manufacturing plants and facilities involves expenses related to land acquisition, construction, machinery, and technology. This can cost anywhere from hundreds of millions to billions of dollars.\n\n3. **Supply Chain and Logistics:**\n   Establishing a reliable supply chain for parts and materials and setting up logistics operations to manage them efficiently is another major expense.\n\n4. **Labor:**\n   Hiring skilled labor for R&D, engineering, assembly, management, marketing, and sales is crucial. Labor costs can substantially vary based on the location and size of the company.\n\n5. **Marketing and Sales:**\n   Building brand awareness and creating distribution networks require substantial marketing and sales efforts. Initial marketing budgets could range from millions to tens of millions of dollars.\n\n6. **Compliance and Legal:**\n   Ensuring all products meet regulatory standards and handling legal aspects of the business can add to the costs. Regulatory testing, certifications, and legal counsel can be very costly.\n\n7. **Technology:**\n   Investment in advanced technologies, such as autonomous driving systems and electric powertrains, can require substantial financial resources.\n\n8. **Miscellaneous Costs:**\n   There are various other costs such as insurance, administrative expenses, and more that will need to be factored in.\n\nIn total, starting a new car company can cost anywhere from several hundred million dollars to several billion dollars, depending on the ambition and scale of the company. For instance, modern electric vehicle startups often raise several billion dollars in funding to cover these extensive initial costs.",
